## Code Standards & Best Practices

### TypeScript

- Use strict TypeScript with no implicit any
- Define interfaces for all props and data structures
- Use type inference where possible
- Create shared types in `/types/index.ts`

```typescript
// Example type definitions
interface Service {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  description: string;
  icon: string;
  slug: string;
}

interface CodingOption {
  category: string;
  features: string[];
  modelSeries: string[];
}
```

### Component Architecture

- Use React Server Components by default
- Add 'use client' only when necessary (forms, interactions, hooks)
- Create reusable, composable components
- Keep components small and single-responsibility
- Use shadcn/ui components for UI primitives

```typescript
// Server Component (default)
export default function ServicesPage() {
  return <ServicesList />;
}

// Client Component (when needed)
("use client");
export function ContactForm() {
  const [state, setState] = useState();
  // ...
}
```

### DRY Principles

- Extract repeated logic into custom hooks
- Create utility functions in `/lib/utils.ts`
- Use component composition over duplication
- Centralize constants in `/lib/constants.ts`

```typescript
// Constants example
export const SERVICES = [
  { id: "maintenance", titleKey: "services.maintenance", icon: "wrench" },
  // ...
] as const;

export const SOCIAL_LINKS = {
  instagram: "https://instagram.com/...",
  facebook: "https://facebook.com/...",
} as const;
```

### Internationalization (i18n)

- Use next-intl for all text content
- Never hardcode text strings
- Structure translation files by page/section
- Use nested keys for organization

```typescript
// Usage in components
import { useTranslations } from "next-intl";

export function Hero() {
  const t = useTranslations("home");
  return <h1>{t("hero.title")}</h1>;
}
```

